I am 100% with wezloc on this.  Moderators should NOT be posting on other class's boards making statements like what was made.  We come here and voice our concerns here, for us.  If a BL wants to know where &quot;we&quot; stand, then they can come here and read &quot;our&quot; opinions, which are varied.  It is not in good faith, for a mage (moderator or otherwise), carrying an easily recognizable name (one such as would be readily remembered), with ties to a community (of which can lead to misconceptions) to go posting on other boards that &quot;we&quot; are/will be behind them.  NO &quot;YOU&quot;, may be behind them getting GVE, I, am NOT, Many of us are NOT, it cannot be said that the mage community is/will be behind them.  There is at least 50% that would disagree with them having equal pets.  It is &quot;my&quot; opinion, that the Raz broke a line of trust.  He is an intelligent, respected, well informed, mage, community leader, moderator, but that doesn't justify his statements.  Please Raz, just don't throw comments out there that &quot;we&quot; as a &quot;whole&quot; would support something, when it can be plainly seen that this community is split on BL's pets at current, Not alone making them equal to our gv's.  You speak for you not the community as a whole.   As I speak for me and me alone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1989<br> <font color=#333333>(10/1/02 5:52:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=363.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsdown.gif" align=absmiddle>  Enough with the inflammatory language!</span>